President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Florida and has authorized federal aid to support recovery efforts from Hurricane Isaac, which occurred from August 27-29, 2012. The funding will be available for emergency work, facility repairs or replacement, and hazard mitigation measures. Gracia B. Szczech has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments.